These 2 (2 fold) ragtop bugs were sitting in the woods growing moss since 1985. The red one is an early 58 and it has the original paint underneath a thin layer of red paint. The blue one is a 61. Both aren’t really missing much and just about complete, not missing the many hard to find parts. Both will be brought back to life and get another chance on the road. Thanks for everything @mopars5150 🤙

One of the buses I wish I had kept. 1967 SO42 Pop top split window walkthrough camper. Last year of the split window before they changed to bay window in 1968. I think it was in Montana and was sitting under some trees for 20 plus years. It was sitting next to a solid 11 window bus that went to a friend. I bought both buses and the owner brought them down to California after we made a deal. The engine fired right up with some new oil and I drove the shit out of this bus before I sold it to my other friend @busnstuff
